1
00:01:18,450 --> 00:01:21,880
[Love Has Fireworks]

2
00:01:21,910 --> 00:01:24,750
[Episode 32]

3
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:27,870
Hello.

4
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:29,630
Hello, Miss Qian.

5
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,070
We're sorry to inform you

6
00:01:31,070 --> 00:01:33,800
that you do not meet
our company's requirements.

7
00:01:36,890 --> 00:01:37,840
I see. Thank you.

8
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:45,160
[Clary Construction Investment]

9
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,690
[Jitonghui Securities]

10
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:07,960
[Zhimei Construction Investment]

11
00:02:08,090 --> 00:02:11,750
[Little Smart Roams the Future]

12
00:02:20,290 --> 00:02:26,700
[Little Smart Roams the Future]

13
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,430
Qian Fei,

14
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:35,310
it's okay.

15
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:39,940
This is only the 10th company
that has rejected you.

16
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,160
Keep trying.

17
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,460
[Hello, Ms. Qian Fei.]

18
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,040
[I'm HR from Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

19
00:03:00,060 --> 00:03:01,490
[I've reviewed your resume.
After a preliminary assessment,]

20
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,820
[we think you'd be a good fit
for our company.]

21
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:04,310
[We'd like to invite you to an interview
at 10:00 AM the day after tomorrow.]

22
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,650
[Please reply to confirm it. Thank you.]

23
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:11,970
[Jingjing]

24
00:03:20,810 --> 00:03:21,520
Hello.

25
00:03:22,190 --> 00:03:23,190
Hello, Jingjing.

26
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:26,120
Did you send my resume
to Xinzouqi Capital?

27
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,340
I've received their interview invitation.

28
00:03:28,340 --> 00:03:29,070
No, I didn't.

29
00:03:31,570 --> 00:03:33,290
That's weird then.

30
00:03:34,410 --> 00:03:37,320
I know the companies I've applied to.

31
00:03:37,810 --> 00:03:40,000
And I only shared my resume with you.

32
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,380
I remember now.

33
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:47,280
I once told Wang Ruohai about this.

34
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:50,630
He said his former boss

35
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,070
left the original bank

36
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:54,040
and started his own venture capital firm.

37
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:56,570
He's doing great
and hiring people right now.

38
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:59,950
He thought this company
would be a good fit for you,

39
00:04:00,670 --> 00:04:02,440
and he could put in a good word for you,

40
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,970
so he asked for your resume.

41
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,550
Well, I actually...

42
00:04:06,110 --> 00:04:08,430
I didn't take what he said seriously.

43
00:04:08,850 --> 00:04:11,480
Never thought he'd actually get it done.

44
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:15,170
Okay, I see.

45
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:17,390
Alright, I'm hanging up.

46
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,400
Who is it?

47
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,770
Hello, are you Ms. Qian Fei?

48
00:04:37,230 --> 00:04:38,110
Yes.

49
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:39,390
Here are your flowers.

50
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,280
Thank you.

51
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:41,960
No problem.

52
00:04:47,210 --> 00:04:50,330
[Let's start over. From Wang Ruohai.]

53
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:59,310
[Blocked Contacts]

54
00:04:59,400 --> 00:04:59,620
[Blocked Contacts]

55
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:03,650
[Calling]

56
00:05:08,690 --> 00:05:10,720
Wang Ruohai, what exactly are you up to?

57
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,750
I just wanted you

58
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,190
to take me off your blacklist.

59
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:14,390
Looks like it worked.

60
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,360
I don't want to talk to you.

61
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:37,920
[Bad Name Took Me Forever]
[Streamer Center]

62
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:44,280
[Bad Name Took Me Forever]
[Streamer Center]

63
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,800
Today's game stream is over.

64
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:55,600
But I'm in a good mood today.

65
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,450
If anyone wants a chit-chat,

66
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:00,530
I can chat with you for a while.

67
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:11,720
Prime Minister,
you're using your mother's account again?

68
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:13,730
[Bad Name Took Me Forever is live.]

69
00:06:12,230 --> 00:06:14,160
I successfully joined the stream.

70
00:06:16,330 --> 00:06:18,810
I can see myself!

71
00:06:19,430 --> 00:06:20,360
[Bad Name Took Me Forever]

72
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,060
Jun, isn't this your mom?

73
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:22,840
Peng Fei, Peng Fei.

74
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:23,400
What's going on?

75
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,600
Look, it's Jun's mom!

76
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:25,960
It really is.

77
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,690
Ma'am...

78
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,870
No, I mean, Blue Baby Bear.

79
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:35,770
[Bad Name Took Me Forever]
[Streamer Center]

80
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,330
-Dang.
-Welcome to my livestream.

81
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:38,940
Meeting you in this way
for the first time,

82
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,159
I'm feeling a bit shy.

83
00:06:42,159 --> 00:06:43,540
Miss Bad Name,

84
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:45,190
I am Blue Baby Bear.

85
00:06:45,230 --> 00:06:49,590
[Bad Name Took Me Forever is live.]

86
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:49,740
Prime Minister and I
have always been following you closely.

87
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:51,720
I-I've sent you many gifts.

88
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,940
I've also been watching your livestream.

89
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:55,600
-It's okay.
-It's not awkward at all.

90
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,630
[Bad Name Took Me Forever]

91
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:56,870
They're having a good time chatting.

92
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,360
[Mom, stop messing around.
Get disconnected now.]

93
00:06:58,380 --> 00:06:59,980
[You're making Bad Name feel awkward.]

94
00:07:00,010 --> 00:07:01,340
[Prime Minister is dating Bad Name?]

95
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,950
[Bad Name, your mother-in-law
has found out about your true colors.]

96
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,940
Wait, what "true colors"?

97
00:07:03,970 --> 00:07:04,500
[Come back to our side.]

98
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:06,310
I understand all this stuff
you say on the internet.

99
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,230
[Peak "mother-in-law & daughter-in-law"
livestream moment]

100
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:10,340
Ma'am, my fans are just
talking nonsense. Don't mind them.

101
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:12,990
Listen,

102
00:07:12,990 --> 00:07:15,670
I'm not Miss Bad Name's mother-in-law.

103
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:16,000
[Hold on...]

104
00:07:15,670 --> 00:07:17,920
But it's true
that Prime Minister is pursuing her.

105
00:07:16,030 --> 00:07:17,060
[What did I miss?]

106
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,120
[No, you came at the perfect time.]

107
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,430
Why are you guys so hyped?

108
00:07:19,550 --> 00:07:21,420
-If they end up falling out
-What are you doing? What is it?

109
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:23,200
because of your provocation,

110
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:25,520
[Bad Name Took Me Forever]

111
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,740
I... I will blame all of you.

112
00:07:27,230 --> 00:07:29,810
Oh, my goodness!
Jun, what does your mom mean by this?

113
00:07:29,810 --> 00:07:32,470
She has won
the mother-in-law over, hasn't she?

114
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:34,100
I thought your mom once said that she

115
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,320
didn't like daughters-in-law
from other cities!

116
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:35,930
Yes!

117
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:38,350
Now that she's won the first prize
in the dance competition,

118
00:07:38,350 --> 00:07:40,310
the household registration issue
is settled, right?

119
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:42,110
-Exactly!
-Sir, please stop it.

120
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:44,320
I'm feeling so embarrassed!

121
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:48,750
Bad Name, I've learned a dance.

122
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,310
Let's interact a bit.

123
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:52,140
[I never saw this coming.]

124
00:07:52,159 --> 00:07:53,490
[For the iconic moment.]

125
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:54,790
[So cute.]

126
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:56,020
[What is happening?]

127
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,500
[Laughing out loud
for the first time today.]

128
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,450
They're dancing! They're dancing!

129
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:00,980
It's trending in the top 30!

130
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,710
It's starting. Let's go.

131
00:08:14,210 --> 00:08:15,370
[Get more people there.] [So cute.]

132
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:17,290
[So many people are watching.] [Don't
know this dance, but she's so pretty.]

133
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:21,070
The fans who like

134
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:23,470
Miss Bad Name,

135
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:26,070
please subscribe

136
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:25,100
[The madam is pretty cute.]

137
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:26,660
[Excellent anchor and beautiful anchor]

138
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:29,930
[Interesting] [Keep playing and dancing]

139
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:28,360
and hit the "like" button.

140
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:29,830
Don't hold back.

141
00:08:41,669 --> 00:08:43,190
The stream is now in the top five!

142
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,670
Jun, your wife and your mom are

143
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:47,310
the model mother-in-law
and daughter-in-law of the internet!

144
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:48,040
Not bad!

145
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:51,040
I didn't expect this would happen,
not even in my dreams!

146
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,000
So nice.

147
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:54,920
Fei, Wang Ruohai is sending me
a barrage of messages.

148
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:57,120
Compared to how he used to be, I feel like

149
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,330
he's a completely different person now.

150
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:01,630
He claimed
that he sincerely wanted to win you back

151
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:04,430
and asked me to persuade you
to go to the interview.

152
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,420
To be honest,

153
00:10:06,450 --> 00:10:08,380
I think he's trying so hard to help you

154
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:10,320
because he owes you in the first place.

155
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:12,590
You don't need to feel any pressure.

156
00:10:12,710 --> 00:10:13,770
Most importantly,

157
00:10:13,820 --> 00:10:15,580
you're making
a major career change this time,

158
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:16,650
and it's so hard.

159
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:18,560
Realistically,

160
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:21,840
I think you should
seize this opportunity he offered you.

161
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:27,200
I see. I will go to the interview.

162
00:10:46,660 --> 00:10:47,930
Come on.

163
00:10:50,290 --> 00:10:52,030
I told you not to drink so much.

164
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:54,100
But you just chugged it down.

165
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:56,810
You're really something.

166
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:57,680
Here, come on.

167
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:17,170
Alright, I'm leaving.

168
00:11:56,570 --> 00:11:59,650
[Pretentious Li]

169
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:03,440
Li Yifei has been on this business trip
for quite a while.

170
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:05,040
It'd be great if he were here.

171
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:07,870
At least he would
wring out a towel for me.

172
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,250
[Pretentious Li]

173
00:12:20,020 --> 00:12:23,230
[Qian Fei]

174
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,170
[Qian Fei]

175
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:50,980
Li Yifei, are you that afraid
that I might cling to you?

176
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:17,060
[Class Monitor]

177
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,490
[Class Monitor]

178
00:13:33,210 --> 00:13:36,430
Young master, you finally called me back.

179
00:13:38,190 --> 00:13:39,790
Hello, Qian Fei?

180
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:42,680
Monitor?

181
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,040
What's up?

182
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:46,640
You must come to be the bridesmaid

183
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:48,240
when Mei and I hold the wedding.

184
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:48,950
It's a deal.

185
00:13:49,910 --> 00:13:52,210
I've been a bridesmaid 3 times already.

186
00:13:52,950 --> 00:13:53,950
If I do it again,

187
00:13:54,650 --> 00:13:56,880
I won't be able to get married myself.

188
00:14:00,810 --> 00:14:01,450
Qian Fei,

189
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:03,670
what's wrong with your voice?

190
00:14:03,670 --> 00:14:04,590
Are you sick?

191
00:14:04,890 --> 00:14:05,690
Where are you?

192
00:14:06,590 --> 00:14:08,930
I must be hallucinating.

193
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:13,810
Why does your voice sound
more and more like Wang Ruohai?

194
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:19,380
[Qian Fei]

195
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:24,670
Qian Fei?

196
00:14:25,310 --> 00:14:25,930
Qian Fei.

197
00:14:27,530 --> 00:14:28,140
Qian Fei?

198
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,480
Wake up, Qian Fei.

199
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:35,700
Wang Ruohai?

200
00:14:37,470 --> 00:14:38,470
Why are you here?

201
00:14:39,830 --> 00:14:40,900
Wake up, Qian Fei.

202
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:42,000
Are you okay?

203
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:43,920
Qian Fei?

204
00:14:45,350 --> 00:14:47,570
Fortunately,
the patient is young and healthy.

205
00:14:47,570 --> 00:14:48,950
If she had arrived any later,

206
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:50,810
it'd have turned into pneumonia.

207
00:14:51,050 --> 00:14:51,850
Doctor.

208
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:54,850
You're awake.

209
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,240
It's okay.

210
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:57,810
Stay in the hospital
for observation for a day,

211
00:14:57,810 --> 00:14:59,610
and the nurse will give you an IV.

212
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:00,640
Thank you.

213
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:46,190
[Qian Fei] [Missed Call]

214
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:02,170
I was having dinner
with my partners yesterday.

215
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,500
I drank a little too much

216
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:05,520
and didn't hear my phone ring.

217
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:28,580
You're awake.

218
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:29,710
Want to get up? Here.

219
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:39,890
What are you looking for?

220
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:41,050
Where is my phone?

221
00:16:41,690 --> 00:16:43,890
I put it away,
so it wouldn't disturb your rest.

222
00:16:43,890 --> 00:16:45,340
I'll let you know
if someone tries to reach you.

223
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:46,450
I need it right now.

224
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:50,440
Here you are.

225
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:52,120
Thanks.

226
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:05,359
I also forgot what I was going to say.

227
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:07,220
Just focus on your business trip.

228
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:38,020
[I also forgot what I was going to say.
Just focus on your business trip.]

229
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,290
Qian Fei,

230
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,710
what are you doing?

231
00:18:03,430 --> 00:18:04,740
I got you some food.

232
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:06,450
Eat it while it's warm.

233
00:18:19,430 --> 00:18:20,010
Here,

234
00:18:20,340 --> 00:18:21,200
let me feed you.

235
00:18:26,430 --> 00:18:26,950
Here.

236
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:29,360
-It's not bad, right?
-Give it to me.

237
00:18:50,950 --> 00:18:52,550
Don't you need to work today?

238
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:54,020
I took the day off.

239
00:18:55,430 --> 00:18:57,990
You're pretty good
at taking care of people now.

240
00:18:57,990 --> 00:18:58,910
I remember

241
00:18:59,150 --> 00:19:00,720
when we were together before.

242
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,400
I used to work late all the time,

243
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,130
yet you never came to pick me up.

244
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:04,970
Now

245
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,330
you're taking such good care of me.

246
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:11,220
You took care of me for 5 years.

247
00:19:11,230 --> 00:19:12,760
I learned just by watching.

248
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:15,300
Actually, it's not that
I didn't know how to do it back then.

249
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,640
It's just that I knew deep down

250
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,890
that no matter how I treated you,

251
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,290
you would never leave me.

252
00:19:19,510 --> 00:19:20,550
So I got lazy.

253
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:21,990
That's quite sincere.

254
00:19:23,710 --> 00:19:24,670
Why do you make it

255
00:19:24,670 --> 00:19:26,230
sound like I did something wrong

256
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:28,630
and gave you too much
of a sense of security?

257
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:30,920
Well, you did teach me a lesson.

258
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,240
Thank you.

259
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:44,130
Qian Fei.

260
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:47,180
If a man

261
00:19:47,290 --> 00:19:49,390
feels like he can easily control you,

262
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:52,000
he will start to cherish you less.

263
00:19:52,690 --> 00:19:54,210
Sometimes, he won't even bother replying

264
00:19:54,210 --> 00:19:55,570
to your messages quickly.

265
00:19:55,570 --> 00:19:56,290
Being busy is

266
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:57,570
just an excuse men use.

267
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:01,520
I don't want

268
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:03,290
to see you get hurt again.

269
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,140
Wang Ruohai,

270
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:05,890
did you check my phone?

271
00:20:06,050 --> 00:20:06,530
Nope.

272
00:20:09,660 --> 00:20:11,520
I just noticed the way you looked—

273
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:13,790
you looked like you were
waiting for someone's reply.

274
00:20:13,790 --> 00:20:15,750
Can you stop making wild guesses?

275
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:16,790
Okay, fine.

276
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:18,280
You are sick.

277
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:19,800
If you say so, then so be it.

278
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:49,500
Mr. Li, come in, please.

279
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,110
You have elegant taste, Mr. Sang.

280
00:20:59,180 --> 00:21:00,710
Come on, Mr. Li, take a seat.

281
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,110
Mr. Li, I heard you've been

282
00:21:06,110 --> 00:21:08,020
on the Fulaxida project
all the time recently.

283
00:21:08,020 --> 00:21:08,680
Yeah.

284
00:21:10,830 --> 00:21:12,090
Looks like your skin's

285
00:21:12,430 --> 00:21:14,010
gotten a healthier tan.

286
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:19,440
Fulaxida has also been facing
constant problems lately.

287
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,410
They've been stuck in the mountains.

288
00:21:21,410 --> 00:21:22,950
Now, those minor shareholders

289
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:25,070
all think their money
has gone down the drain.

290
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:28,530
They keep calling me all day long,
wanting to track the project.

291
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:29,620
Meanwhile,

292
00:21:30,310 --> 00:21:32,970
Mr. Sang, you have a better temper
and stay calm.

293
00:21:33,730 --> 00:21:35,730
You're even in the mood for running.

294
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:51,200
Honestly,

295
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,730
I've heard a little about

296
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:57,400
what's happening in Fulaxida.

297
00:21:57,650 --> 00:21:58,680
But I believe that

298
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,770
with your capability, Mr. Li,

299
00:22:00,770 --> 00:22:03,090
you certainly won't let me suffer losses.

300
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:04,090
Not necessarily.

301
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:07,540
Take a look at this document.

302
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,600
It concerns your interests.

303
00:22:19,190 --> 00:22:20,070
[Share Termination Contract]

304
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:21,050
[Party A: Sanglin Group Co., Ltd.]

305
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:22,220
[Termination Contract]

306
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:43,870
[Sanglin Group Co., Ltd.]

307
00:22:41,690 --> 00:22:43,840
Mr. Li, what do you mean by this?

308
00:22:45,470 --> 00:22:47,390
I mean exactly
what is written in this document.

309
00:22:47,390 --> 00:22:50,790
Let's terminate the contract.
We're no longer cooperating.

310
00:22:51,710 --> 00:22:55,220
Mr. Sang, keep the drama you staged

311
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,810
to yourself.

312
00:22:57,680 --> 00:23:00,330
Fulaxida has never been,
and will never be,

313
00:23:01,020 --> 00:23:02,360
a tool for you

314
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:04,080
to easily rake in money.

315
00:23:04,470 --> 00:23:05,280
Understand?

316
00:23:07,170 --> 00:23:08,390
Do you know

317
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,000
what you are doing?

318
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,470
I couldn't be clearer about it.

319
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:17,830
You want to kick me out, right?

320
00:23:22,570 --> 00:23:23,320
Fine.

321
00:23:25,230 --> 00:23:26,580
But before that,

322
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:28,490
I also have a contract

323
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:30,570
for you, Mr. Li,

324
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:32,620
to take a look.

325
00:24:08,370 --> 00:24:10,540
[Sanglin Group Co., Ltd.]

326
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:17,510
Y-Yifei,

327
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:18,940
hear me out.

328
00:24:19,170 --> 00:24:21,630
I really didn't know
signing that was a trap.

329
00:24:21,830 --> 00:24:22,860
They told me that

330
00:24:22,990 --> 00:24:24,700
if I signed this technical contract

331
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:26,360
as the legal representative,

332
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:28,400
it would be like adding a lock

333
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,810
to the project's funding.

334
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:31,220
So you signed it?

335
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:33,120
They said

336
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,840
this contract could be terminated
at any time.

337
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:40,360
Didn't you know that

338
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:42,230
the contract had been tampered with?

339
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:44,490
Yifei, don't... don't scare me.

340
00:24:44,990 --> 00:24:45,750
I was wrong.

341
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:47,950
I'll accept any punishment you give me.

342
00:24:48,260 --> 00:24:49,500
What should we do now?

343
00:24:51,420 --> 00:24:52,560
But things are no longer

344
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:54,020
the way you think they are.

345
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,240
Explain it clearly, Li Yifei!

346
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:01,640
Don't tell me Fulaxida will end up

347
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:03,040
belonging to Sang Shiqi!

348
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:07,040
Today, I came to force Mr. Sang
to withdraw his investment in Fulaxida,

349
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,790
but I was actually
just trying to provoke him.

350
00:25:08,790 --> 00:25:11,190
I wanted to see
the last thing up his sleeve.

351
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:15,530
Y-You mean

352
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:17,760
you already knew he wouldn't agree?

353
00:25:17,870 --> 00:25:18,290
Yes.

354
00:25:19,860 --> 00:25:21,230
And I made him expose

355
00:25:21,230 --> 00:25:22,690
the real power behind him.

356
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:23,920
Who is it?

357
00:25:24,810 --> 00:25:25,930
Liao Jinshan.

358
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,010
Are you sure?

359
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:32,010
Today, he took out that tampered contract

360
00:25:32,010 --> 00:25:33,210
to force me to give in.

361
00:25:33,890 --> 00:25:36,150
I can't be more familiar with this trick.

362
00:25:37,790 --> 00:25:40,610
When Qiansheng Group
went public in the US,

363
00:25:40,870 --> 00:25:43,870
Liao Jinshan used this exact trick
against my family.

364
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:45,140
It's just that I was

365
00:25:45,610 --> 00:25:47,710
too young to take part in it back then.

366
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:50,490
I heard about it from my dad later.

367
00:25:51,470 --> 00:25:54,140
Should I say you're lucky or you're smart?

368
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:57,100
All right.
Now that we know who our enemy is,

369
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,940
it'll be easier for us
to fight the next battle.

370
00:25:58,940 --> 00:25:59,940
It's not over yet.

371
00:26:03,950 --> 00:26:05,320
Besides Liao Jinshan,

372
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,340
there's someone else.

373
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:11,250
You... You mean there's one more mole?

374
00:26:11,750 --> 00:26:12,180
Yep.

375
00:26:14,290 --> 00:26:16,690
Only people familiar with my usual style

376
00:26:17,710 --> 00:26:19,290
would clearly know that

377
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:21,520
I would use shares to confront Mr. Sang.

378
00:26:24,980 --> 00:26:26,900
Oh, Li Yifei,

379
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:29,360
so you've been setting up such a big trap!

380
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:31,180
You even kept it from me.

381
00:26:31,180 --> 00:26:32,210
That's not cool!

382
00:26:33,470 --> 00:26:34,380
I have no choice.

383
00:26:34,380 --> 00:26:36,110
Only by hiding it from everyone

384
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:38,330
can I catch the real mole.

385
00:26:43,020 --> 00:26:43,570
Okay.

386
00:26:50,430 --> 00:26:54,110
[Zhonggeng Global Creative Center]

387
00:26:53,630 --> 00:26:55,640
Qian Fei, I've seen you before.

388
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:57,840
I saw you at the company entrance
when you were waiting

389
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,320
for Wang Ruohai to get off work.

390
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:00,450
I've seen you, too.

391
00:27:00,470 --> 00:27:02,510
After founding Xinzouqi Capital,

392
00:27:02,540 --> 00:27:03,910
you've made frequent appearances
in the media.

393
00:27:03,910 --> 00:27:05,320
Having made a new venture capital firm

394
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:06,560
so competitive

395
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:08,090
in such a short time—

396
00:27:08,190 --> 00:27:09,720
I think it's truly amazing.

397
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:10,730
Thank you.

398
00:27:12,220 --> 00:27:14,140
We've all reviewed your resume.

399
00:27:12,330 --> 00:27:16,010
[Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

400
00:27:14,430 --> 00:27:15,520
We've also conducted

401
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:18,190
background checks on your work history

402
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:19,880
and why you left He Jing Securities.

403
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:20,820
Frankly speaking,

404
00:27:20,820 --> 00:27:22,400
even if we set aside

405
00:27:22,430 --> 00:27:23,870
the reason you were dismissed,

406
00:27:23,870 --> 00:27:25,520
I believe this incident

407
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:28,670
has a major impact on your career
in investment banking.

408
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,210
It's not devastating, though.

409
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:34,660
I think you could
transition into the back office

410
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:36,730
[Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

411
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:36,940
or pass other qualification exams

412
00:27:37,150 --> 00:27:38,890
to get back into investment banking.

413
00:27:38,890 --> 00:27:39,970
But why

414
00:27:39,860 --> 00:27:43,780
[Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

415
00:27:40,260 --> 00:27:42,790
would you choose
a small venture capital firm

416
00:27:42,790 --> 00:27:43,710
like ours?

417
00:27:44,750 --> 00:27:45,600
I've worked

418
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,860
at He Jing Securities since graduation.

419
00:27:48,050 --> 00:27:49,710
It helped me grow significantly

420
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:51,790
and broadened my horizons
in the financial industry.

421
00:27:51,790 --> 00:27:53,920
Especially in back-end data analysis

422
00:27:53,950 --> 00:27:55,430
and front-end project preparation,

423
00:27:55,430 --> 00:27:57,100
it allowed me
to accumulate a lot of experience.

424
00:27:57,100 --> 00:27:58,860
As for the reason I was dismissed,

425
00:27:58,860 --> 00:28:03,500
[Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

426
00:27:59,270 --> 00:28:00,450
I could have simply used

427
00:28:00,450 --> 00:28:02,150
the company's internal adjustments

428
00:28:02,150 --> 00:28:03,630
as an excuse to explain it.

429
00:28:04,290 --> 00:28:06,070
But actually, regarding this incident,

430
00:28:06,070 --> 00:28:07,820
the biggest lesson it taught me is that

431
00:28:07,820 --> 00:28:10,180
when facing the industry's unspoken rules,

432
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:12,440
you either accept them and adapt to them,

433
00:28:12,810 --> 00:28:14,270
or you step away from them.

434
00:28:14,490 --> 00:28:17,040
And I chose
to stay true to my original intention.

435
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:19,970
I don't want to force myself
for the sake of my future.

436
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:23,230
So I chose to leave investment banking
and come here.

437
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:25,460
How do you know that

438
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:27,700
you can realize your original intention

439
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:29,500
here at Xinzouqi Capital?

440
00:28:31,090 --> 00:28:32,400
Actually, before coming to the interview,

441
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:35,430
I investigated every project
Xinzouqi Capital has invested in

442
00:28:35,430 --> 00:28:37,510
since its establishment.

443
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:39,320
Although I wasn't involved in them,

444
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,710
I could tell that

445
00:28:40,710 --> 00:28:42,660
under your leadership, Xinzouqi Capital

446
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:43,670
is not just

447
00:28:43,670 --> 00:28:45,510
a profit-seeking venture capital firm

448
00:28:45,510 --> 00:28:47,510
but a capital bridge
with a forward-looking vision

449
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:49,800
and a sense of social responsibility.

450
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:52,930
Then how do you define

451
00:28:52,950 --> 00:28:55,700
the essence of equity investment?

452
00:28:55,890 --> 00:28:57,640
I think equity investment is

453
00:28:57,670 --> 00:28:59,710
actually a relationship
between zero and one.

454
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:01,120
It's either zero or one.

455
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:03,120
There is actually no middle ground.

456
00:29:03,420 --> 00:29:05,270
If you win,

457
00:29:05,270 --> 00:29:06,400
you get returns.

458
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:08,260
If you lose, you lose everything.

459
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,750
There's only one way to win,

460
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:12,560
which is to help enterprises

461
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:14,800
create real value for society.

462
00:29:24,580 --> 00:29:25,310
We're glad

463
00:29:25,770 --> 00:29:28,040
to have you join us at Xinzouqi Capital.

464
00:29:28,070 --> 00:29:30,640
Let's work together

465
00:29:30,670 --> 00:29:32,130
to help more enterprises.

466
00:29:32,410 --> 00:29:33,200
Thank you.

467
00:29:33,070 --> 00:29:35,690
[Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

468
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:37,360
Look, No. 9 and No. 10,

469
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:38,120
as well as No. 1,

470
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:39,880
have these field controllers installed.

471
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,080
The rest of them are still

472
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,880
under construction currently.

473
00:29:48,490 --> 00:29:49,470
Are you exhausted

474
00:29:49,470 --> 00:29:51,600
from running around the past few days?

475
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,670
Well, if so, you should go back first.

476
00:29:55,670 --> 00:29:58,130
We're almost done anyway.
That's almost it.

477
00:29:58,670 --> 00:30:00,870
Okay, thank you for your hard work, too.

478
00:30:01,190 --> 00:30:01,710
Okay.

479
00:30:02,730 --> 00:30:04,130
By the way, um,

480
00:30:04,210 --> 00:30:05,670
Qian Fei has found a new job.

481
00:30:05,670 --> 00:30:06,880
My wife called me.

482
00:30:07,030 --> 00:30:09,130
She said Qian Fei's working
at Xinzouqi Capital now.

483
00:30:09,130 --> 00:30:11,130
She's switched to venture capital.

484
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,510
Xinzouqi?

485
00:30:15,190 --> 00:30:16,520
How did she get in there?

486
00:30:19,990 --> 00:30:22,450
That's not something confidential, right?

487
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:25,910
I think it was because of Wang Ruohai.

488
00:30:26,270 --> 00:30:29,100
He used to be the subordinate
of Xinzouqi's boss.

489
00:30:30,010 --> 00:30:31,870
After hearing
that Qian Fei was looking for a job,

490
00:30:31,870 --> 00:30:34,600
he put in a good word for her
with Xinzouqi's boss.

491
00:30:36,190 --> 00:30:37,390
When did this happen?

492
00:30:38,630 --> 00:30:40,560
In the last couple of days, I think.

493
00:30:49,450 --> 00:30:51,650
What? Are you panicking?

494
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:58,850
It just occurred to me that

495
00:31:00,730 --> 00:31:03,370
Qian Fei sent me WeChat messages
a few days ago.

496
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,720
I guess it was about her job hunting.

497
00:31:08,740 --> 00:31:11,270
She must have been very helpless
at that time,

498
00:31:12,430 --> 00:31:14,610
but I couldn't help her at all.

499
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:19,570
Hey, why are you being so indecisive now?

500
00:31:20,170 --> 00:31:21,220
Actually,

501
00:31:22,670 --> 00:31:25,000
I've always been sure
that I like Qian Fei.

502
00:31:26,340 --> 00:31:27,270
But does Qian Fei

503
00:31:30,010 --> 00:31:31,250
really like me, too?

504
00:31:31,790 --> 00:31:32,890
Or in other words,

505
00:31:34,030 --> 00:31:34,760
would she...

506
00:31:35,950 --> 00:31:36,950
accept me?

507
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:40,560
Hold on, hold on...

508
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:43,190
Y-You two have lived together for so long.

509
00:31:43,190 --> 00:31:44,030
Can't you even tell

510
00:31:44,030 --> 00:31:45,630
whether she likes you or not?

511
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:47,800
Hey, when it comes to women,

512
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:49,800
aren't you an expert?

513
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:52,630
It's different now.

514
00:31:53,710 --> 00:31:56,560
Liking someone and loving someone
are even more different.

515
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:57,820
I'm serious this time.

516
00:31:58,330 --> 00:32:00,100
I want to marry her.

517
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:04,460
Then what are you doing here?

518
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:07,390
It's a long story.

519
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:09,880
I wanted to use this trip

520
00:32:09,900 --> 00:32:11,160
to completely sort out

521
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:12,160
my thoughts.

522
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:15,640
I was nervous, after all.

523
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,620
But I happened to overlook one thing.

524
00:32:20,650 --> 00:32:23,780
She couldn't possibly just stay in place
waiting for me.

525
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:27,700
There's nothing between us yet.

526
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:30,160
She has no obligation to do so, either.

527
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,050
Stop it.

528
00:32:32,740 --> 00:32:33,820
All right, look.

529
00:32:35,770 --> 00:32:37,450
Tell me how you feel

530
00:32:37,470 --> 00:32:38,630
right now.

531
00:32:40,740 --> 00:32:42,690
I never stop yearning to see her.

532
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:47,010
But there are no more flights today.

533
00:32:48,910 --> 00:32:50,770
I'll fly early tomorrow morning.

534
00:32:51,150 --> 00:32:52,250
I'll leave this to you.

535
00:32:52,250 --> 00:32:53,180
I believe in you.

536
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:55,120
Okay!

537
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:56,520
You got this!

538
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:08,950
[Exit]

539
00:33:19,350 --> 00:33:22,480
Help me book a table with a view
at an Italian restaurant.

540
00:33:24,150 --> 00:33:25,000
At 5:00 PM.

541
00:33:26,470 --> 00:33:27,110
For two.

542
00:33:28,890 --> 00:33:29,820
Okay, thank you.

543
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:42,130
[Xinzouqi Capital Co., Ltd.]

544
00:33:45,820 --> 00:33:48,760
[Pretentious Li]

545
00:33:57,250 --> 00:33:57,830
Hello?

546
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:01,010
Landlady, I'm back.

547
00:34:06,380 --> 00:34:07,050
Well...

